.TH "HOST-INETD" "8" "" "Project Kennel" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
host\-inetd \- inbound BIND mirror delegate
.SH SYNOPSIS
(internal \(em forked by kenneld(8), not invoked directly)
.SH DESCRIPTION
host\-inetd is kenneld's host\-side inbound\-BIND delegate (the reverse of host\-netproxy). For each policy\-mirrored port it binds the kennel's loopback alias on the host, accepts, splices locally, and pushes the conduit's kennel end back to kenneld. It holds no policy. See the §7.5.7 mirror.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBkenneld\fR(8), \fBkennel\fR(1)
